We use partial of the public released code Awesome-Align for XLM-R version. (https://github.com/neulab/awesome-align/tree/xlmr)
The copyright statements and comments of the original code are preserved.
We mainly modify the file "modeling_roberta.py" and "modeling.py" to implement self-guided contrastive learning word-alignment method. We modify "BertGuideHead" class and add "BertContrastiveHead" class in "modeling.py".

Requirements:
python == 3.7.10
pytorch == 1.6.0
transformer == 4.11.3
numpy == 1.21.0
tqdm == 4.62.3